cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper presents a new method for magnetic resonance imaging using deep learning and convolutional neural networks for water-fat separation. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of DL for image processing also relates to multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper involves training a neural network, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
